snippet: The two men, identified by Somali officials as members of the Shabab militant group, were convicted of killing four lawmakers and an intelligence officer.
abstract: Two members of Shabab militant group are publicly executed in Somalia after being convicted of killing four Somali lawmakers and an intelligence officer in series of attacks in 2014.
lead_paragraph: The two men, identified by Somali officials as members of the Shabab militant group, were convicted of killing four lawmakers and an intelligence officer.

headline.main: Somalia Executes 2 Militants Convicted of Assassinations
